focusing on the \u0022Work Queue\u0022 section. It features a sidebar menu with options like \u0022Settings,\u0022 \u0022General,\u0022 \u0022Maps,\u0022 \u0022Users \u0026 Security,\u0022 \u0022Active Sessions,\u0022 \u0022Add User,\u0022 and \u0022Application Roles.\u0022 The main content area lists application roles with columns for \u0022Name,\u0022 \u0022Description,\u0022 \u0022User Remarks,\u0022 \u0022Time Created,\u0022 and \u0022System.\u0022 The highlighted role is \u0022FRM Queues,\u0022 created on \u002204/02/2025 17:\u0022. Additionally, there is a section titled \u0022Assigned User Roles\u0022 showing \u0022Queue Admin\u0022 with a \u0022Read Only (Screen)\u0022 indicator. Navigation buttons for saving and refreshing the page are visible at the top.\n\n\n  \n   Creating New User Roles \n User roles are tied to a specific application instance and must be created within the application. \n To create a new user role: \n \n Use the  plus  or  duplicate  icon. \n Assign application roles to it. \n \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/7/7eba615fac34538248b1cc4ecd8b4b97d2f25e0c.png]\nDescription: The image displays a user interface for the \u0022Origam\u0022 application, specifically the \u0022User Roles\u0022 section within \u0022Application Roles.\u0022 Key UI elements include the \u0022User Roles\u0022 header, and three columns titled \u0022Name,\u0022 \u0022Alias,\u0022 and \u0022Application Role.\u0022 Under the \u0022User Roles\u0022 section, two entries are visible: \u0022Super User (Built-in)\u0022 and \u0022Queue Admin.\u0022 There are buttons for adding new roles and copying roles, indicated by plus and clipboard icons. Below this, the \u0022Assigned Application Roles\u0022 section shows an entry for \u0022FRM_WorkQueue\u0022 along with checkboxes labeled \u0022Read Only (Screen)\u0022 and \u0022IsInitialScreen.\u0022 The purpose of the interface appears to be the management and assignment of user roles within the application.\n\n\n  \n If you want to restrict standard users from accessing application settings, you can create a custom user role and assign it only the  FRM_UserProfile  default application role. This will limit their access only to the  My User Profile  form within the default application settings. \n   Creating New Users \n To manage users, go to  Users . To add a new user, navigate to  Add User : \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/8/8c5861b6b3754539c73575f373596c473e783d4f.png]\nDescription: The image displays a user interface for adding a new user within a software application. The left sidebar includes a navigation menu with options such as \u0022Work Queue,\u0022 \u0022Favourites,\u0022 \u0022Settings\u0022 (subsections: \u0022General,\u0022 \u0022Maps,\u0022 \u0022Users \u0026 Security,\u0022 \u0022Active Sessions,\u0022 \u0022Application Roles\u0022), and prominently features an \u0022Add User\u0022 button. The right side presents the \u0022Enter User Information\u0022 form, which includes fields for \u0022First Name\u0022 (Viktor), \u0022Name\u0022 (Ter), \u0022Login Name\u0022 (vikter), \u0022Login E-mail\u0022 (viktor.ter@advantages.cz), and \u0022Password.\u0022 Below these fields, there are checkboxes for user roles, highlighting \u0022Super User (Built-in)\u0022 and \u0022Standard User,\u0022 with the latter selected. The apparent purpose of this interface is to facilitate the creation of a new user account within the application.\n\n\n  \n Enter the required details, set a password (minimum 6 characters; configurable in  app settings ), and assign at least one  user role . \n Save the changes to create the user. \n To activate the user immediately, go to  Users  and click  Confirm Email : \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/2/20f5dbe899faaeb88e5aa5eb2fc51d6001d49310.png]\nDescription: The image displays a user interface from an application named \u0022ORIGAM.\u0022 The left sidebar includes options labeled \u0022Work Queue\u0022 and \u0022Favourites.\u0022 The main section features a header labeled \u0022Users,\u0022 where a prominent button reads \u0022Confirm Email\u0022 in red, indicating a feature for confirming email addresses. Additional buttons include \u0022Save,\u0022 \u0022Refresh,\u0022 \u0022Remove Access,\u0022 and \u0022Enforce 2FA.\u0022 The purpose of the interface appears to be for managing user accounts and email confirmations within the application.\n\n\n","vector_provider":"AI.Ollama.OllamaTextEmbeddingGenerator","vector_generator":"__","last_update":"2026-05-01T23:47:03"},"vector":[-0.017650517,0.004921618,-0.07758934,-0.0018597018,-0.004415044,-0.030865967,0.021043213,-9.1699294E-05,0.008973162,-0.0075454693,-0.0005896613,-0.018085703,0.008336693,0.017783161,-0.0072968835,0.009386468,-0.016780302,-0.010042526,0.0026311257,0.013178768,0.0054371096,-0.015992012,0.018499255,-0.008811207,0.006320501,0.02132755,-0.006303068,-0.00085028895,0.011223744,-0.019628149,0.021346364,-0.07470305,-0.019962918,-0.022641959,-0.0070373868,0.027538773,-0.009866898,0.01911173,-0.05102114,0.0062922193,-0.0076683173,-0.022278229,-0.011029697,0.030867139,-0.0011607636,-0.022290817,7.4481875E-05,0.008161147,0.06405856,-0.021175696,-0.029449504,-0.019763527,0.01526878,-0.052623417,0.03153587,0.07802557,-0.03580972,-0.03812456,-0.030226018,0.01615684,-0.0020537819,0.022058705,-0.029594047,-0.042553086,0.0004678129,0.010181881,-0.022999682,-0.011964519,-0.021513185,-0.056907684,-0.042150747,0.047848433,-0.04592912,-0.040416438,-0.07495751,-0.0031115771,0.029877836,-0.00023655972,-0.017213378,0.039472096,-0.015848653,-0.004525156,0.009308434,0.0055751996,0.018286783,0.017160285,-0.026689813,0.07635206,-0.012978401,0.03535042,-0.050978523,-0.007384738,0.0723743,-0.050696664,-0.025786497,0.00032804918,-0.008302437,-0.009334932,-0.0021923436,-0.0066016694,-0.017836126,0.010416312,-0.01937727,-0.003471266,-0.046831243,-0.01793972,-0.015